lenovo/ideapad/16ach6/README.md-This laptop comes with an AMD CPU+GPU and dedicated NVIDIA graphics. Unlike the similarly named [Legion 5 Pro 16ACH6*H*](../../legion/16ach6h/), there is no direct dedicated graphics setting.
lenovo/ideapad/16ach6/README.md-
lenovo/ideapad/16ach6/README.md:The `nvidia.hardware.powerManagement.enable` option is not enabled in this configuration, since it seemed to cause issues when waking up from suspend, while also not providing much in terms of power saving. I've tested with `finegrained` both enabled and disabled, and it caused the screen to go dark a few moments after waking up from suspend. Most times this only happened once and the screen came back after a few moments, but on some occasions it kept occurring repeatedly.
